	abstract = {One of the primary mission objectives for the Roman Space Telescope is 
to investigate the nature of dark energy with a variety of methods.
Observations of Type Ia supernovae (SNIa) will be one of the principal
anchors of the Roman cosmology program, through traditional luminosity
distance measurements. This SNIa cosmology program can provide another
