intercalibration of the SNLS and SDSS surveys and reduced systematic
uncertainties in the photometric calibration, performed blindly with
respect to the cosmology analysis; and 3) a thorough investigation of
systematic errors associated with the SALT2 modeling of SN Ia light
curves. Results: We produce recalibrated SN Ia light curves and
associated distances for the SDSS-II and SNLS samples. The large SDSS-II
sample provides an effective, independent, low-z anchor for the Hubble
diagram and reduces the systematic error from calibration systematics in
the low-z SN sample. For a flat ΛCDM cosmology, we find
Ωm =0.295 ± 0.034 (stat+sys), a value consistent
